Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph wkg-job:// list

Purpose:
  Show queue jobs. By default this shows active jobs: `queued`, `running`, and `paused`.

Usage:
  wikigraph wkg-job:// list [--all] [--active] [--input <archive-uri>] [--json]

Options:
  --all                 Include terminal history: `succeeded`, `failed`, and `canceled`.
  --active              Show only active jobs. This is the default.
  --input <archive-uri> Filter jobs to one archive.
  --json                Print a stable machine-readable snapshot.

Human columns:
  JOB       Short job id.
  STATE     queued, running, paused, succeeded, failed, or canceled.
  STEP      Current running step: reading-graph, reading-summary, knowledge-graph, or `-`.
  TARGET    Requested target: reading-graph, reading-summary, or knowledge-graph.
  CHAPTER   Chapter id.
  ARCHIVE   Archive file name.

Agent use:
  - Use `--json` for structured inspection.
  - Use `wkg-job://<job-id> get --json` for one job.
  - Use `wkg-job://<job-id> watch --jsonl` for durable event history and progress.

Examples:
  wikigraph wkg-job:// list
  wikigraph wkg-job:// list --input wkg://book.wikg --json
  wikigraph wkg-job:// list --all
